<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFCE6A71FA879AFB19A5B607" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFCE6A71FA879AFB19A5B607" blockId="53.[1400,2610,2008,3461]" pageId="53" pageNumber="811">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFCE6A71FA879AFB18DCB78D" bold="true" box="[1403,1756,3234,3263]" pageId="53" pageNumber="811">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List (and also listed as Data Deficient as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCE6A71F9079A9C19A0B7D4" baseAuthorityName="Tate" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[1787,1952,3269,3302]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anthonyi">H. anthonyi</taxonomicName>
). Joffre’s Pipistrelle is known from only a few specimens scattered over a relatively wide area. Nothing is known of its ecology and threats, and further research is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
